---
title: Steakhouse-Style Pork Chops with a Creamy Pan Sauce, Roasted Potatoes & Lemony Broccoli
description: Our chefs gave pork chops a steak-like treatment: tender chops are coated in a bold and savory steak spice, seared, then drizzled with a creamy pan sauce. And like any great steakhouse-style meal, the sides are just as impressive. Roasted potatoes and lemony broccoli round everything out. Now all you need is someone to bring you a dessert menu!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64230456a46ae91f080af47f-a1de8e10.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/648884de0b7af205da01b33e.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/steakhouse-style-pork-chops-648884de0b7af205da01b33e
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 49 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 860 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince half the @yellow onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @?cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet; roast on top rack for 20-25 minutes total.)

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the broccoli then).

Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown and broccoli is tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

While veggies roast, pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt, then coat with as much @bold & savory steak spice{1%tablespoon} as will stick.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> If crust begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced onion; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{¼%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} until combined. Season generously with pepper.

Toss broccoli with lemon zest.

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Spoon pan sauce over pork. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.